The structure of nucleic acids is indeed sugar. Two different sugars can be found in nucleic acids. Deoxyribonucleic acid (DNA)contains deoxyribose, hence its name, whereas ribonucleic acid (RNA) contains a sugar called ribose. The structures of ribose and deoxyribose are:
